DATABASE SETUP
	
	1.Download and Install MSSQL
	2.Execute the script files for creating Schema for ControlCentre
	3.Execute the insert queries as well.

PHYSICAL FOLDERS
	Make below folders in your Machine:
	Base Folder
		1.C:\Users\Administrator\sa

	Folder for holding Language json
		2.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\config
		3.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\config\language
	
	Folder for saving logs for all 4 services 
		4.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\logs
		5.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\logs\ccapi
		6.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\logs\ccapi\archive
		7.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\logs\ccui
		8.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\logs\ccui\archive
		
	Backup folder
		9.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\uploadedfiles\carouselbannerzip
	       10.C:\Users\Administrator\sa\uploadedfiles\assetzip

TOMCAT

	1. Download the tomcat repo from github
	2. Change directory into tomcat repo folder\conf
	3. Change the ssl certificate path inside the server.xml file that is inside the tomcat repo folder\conf
	4. Save the server.xml file
	5. Change directory into tomcat repo folder\bin
	6. Open Command Prompt in the bin folder
	7. Start the tomcat sever using startup.bat inside bin folder
	8. To Stop the running applications use shutdown.bat inside bin folder

